<Meta title="Styles/Patterns/Introduction" />

# Pattern System

The Pattern System provides the visual implementation rules for the **Pattern Packs** defined in the PLUS Design System.

Each section below serves as the **Single Source of Truth** for the context, tokens, elevation, and interaction rules for that category.

## Design System Context: Implementation Rules

**System Directive:** This documentation is the single source of truth for UI implementation. Adhere strictly to these token mappings and logic. Do not use hex codes or infer values.

### 1. Surface Color and Elevation Based on Context
*Use specific tokens based on the component type and context. Elevation implies visual layering.*

| Component | Context / State | Required Token | Elevation |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Surface** | Base Background | `surface` | 0 |
| **Surface Container** | General Wrapper | `surface-container` | 0 |
| **Card** | Default | `surface-container-lowest` | 1 |
| **Modal** | Default | `surface-container-high` | 3 |
| **Section** | Default | `surface-container-low` (or `no-fill`) | 0 |
| **Table** | Default | `no-fill` | 0 |
| **Element** | Active State | `surface-container-highest` | -- |
| **Element** | Default / Read State | `surface` | 0 |

### 2. Neutral Color Tokens for Typography & Borders
*Apply these tokens to content sitting ON TOP of the surfaces defined above.*

* **Primary Text:** `on-surface`
    * *Usage:* Headings, primary data, active body text.
* **Secondary Text:** `on-surface-variant`
    * *Usage:* Subtitles, metadata, timestamps.
* **Outer Borders:** `outline`
    * *Usage:* External component perimeters (e.g., Card border).
* **Inner Dividers:** `outline-variant`
    * *Usage:* Internal lines and separators.

### 3. Universal Interaction Logic
*Applicable to ALL interactive items (Cards, Table Rows, List Items, Buttons).*

**Logic:** Interaction states are **additive overlays**. Do not replace the base fill token defined in Section 1. Instead, overlay the `on-surface` opacity token on top of it.

| State | Overlay Token (Layer on top) | Border / Stroke Change | Opacity Rule |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Hover** | `on-surface` @ 8% opacity | None | 100% |
| **Pressed** | `on-surface` @ 16% opacity | None | 100% |
| **Focus** | `on-surface` @ 12% opacity | Change Border to `Inverse Primary` | 100% |
| **Disabled** | `on-surface` @ 8% opacity | None | **Set Total Component Opacity to 38%** |
